The Scarlet King, Wondertainment and the Broken God are all SCPs. The fact that they're 001 proposals doesn't make them any less non-canonical because there is no canon. Vincent Anderson is a non-001 SCP, and if someone doesn't like that they're free to ignore it, just as they are this one.

I killed Fuller, yes, but I strongly imply that he could come back. And again, since there is no canon, anyone who wants to write about Herman Fuller as if this doesn't exist is free to do so. I have not ruined the fun for anyone. While it is true that most of the Herman Fuller stuff posted in the past couple of years has at least some input from myself, there are at least a couple I had nothing to do with, and at least one of those (Fish Are Friends Not Clowns) remains firmly unaffiliated with Dread  Circuses if they want to.

Please read There Are No Strings On Me for how Herman managed to survive the Darkness Between Dimensions.







